    "number": 21121,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "[Bugfix] Allocate less memory in non-batched CUTLASS MoE",
    "user": {
      "login": "ElizaWszola",
      "id": 26595727,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI2NTk1NzI3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/26595727?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/ElizaWszola",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ElizaWszola/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "The way we obtain `N` from `_moe_problem_size()` caused the function to allocate up to twice as much memory in `cutlass_moe`'s `workspace_shapes()` as needed. The fix brings down the size of workspaces to what actually reflects the size needed to store `cutlass_moe`'s intermediate tensors.\n\n#### Testing\n\nTested for correctness with offline inference for `nm-testing/DeepSeek-Coder-V2-Lite-Instruct-FP8` and\n```\npytest tests/kernels/moe/test_cutlass_moe.py -k test_cutlass_moe_8_bit_EP_large\npytest tests/kernels/moe/test_cutlass_moe.py -k test_cutlass_moe_8_bit_cuda_graph\n```",
    "created_at": "2025-07-17T14:58:22Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-07-18T10:55:52Z",
    "closed_at": "2025-07-18T10:55:52Z",
    "merged_at": "2025-07-18T10:55:52Z",
